The Philadelphia 76ers forced a Game 7 on Saturday following an 82-75 victory over the Boston Celtics in Game 6 on Wednesday. Jrue Holiday scored 20 points, including two huge free throws with 31.4 seconds remaining, Elton Brand added 13 points and the Sixers improved to 5-0 this postseason following a loss. Andre Iguodala and Evan Turner had 12 each while Lou Williams contributed 11 in the balanced effort. Game 7 will be Saturday in Boston
